  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken thigh </strong>to the dish and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669725550385-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669725550385-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669725550385-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669725550385-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1669725550385-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into wedges</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Once browned, add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> to the dish with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and<strong> </strong>bring to the boil over a high heat, once boiling put the dish in the oven and cook, covered, for an initial 35 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669725556649-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669725556649-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669725556649-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669725556649-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1669725556649-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p><p>Take some <strong>butter</strong> out of the fridge and set aside to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669725560793-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669725560793-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669725560793-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669725560793-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1669725560793-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>coconut flakes</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden (reserve the pan!)</p><p>Once golden, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>toasted coconut flakes</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!) to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and bash into a powder (as finely as you can!), then mix the <strong>crushed coconut</strong> with your <strong>sultanas</strong> and <strong>nigella seeds</strong> – this is your <strong>peshwari filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1669725564545-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1669725564545-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1669725564545-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1669725564545-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1669725564545-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pizza base mix</strong> and <strong>peshwari filling </strong>to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add 75ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [110ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>(careful, you may not need all of it!), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the dough out onto a<strong> </strong>lightly oiled<strong> </strong>work surface and cut into 2<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>balls per person</p><p>Press each <strong>dough ball</strong> out into an oval disc with your fingers – these are your<strong> naans</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1669725569618-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1669725569618-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1669725569618-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1669725569618-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1669725569618-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong></p><p>After 35 min, remove the dish from the oven, and add the <strong>spinach</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and return the dish to the oven, uncovered, for a final 10 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the sauce has thickened</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1669725574872-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1669725574872-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1669725574872-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1669725574872-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1669725574872-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat the reserved pan over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>naans </strong>to the pan and cook<strong> </strong>for 2-3 min on each side or until puffed up and golden brown</p><p>While the naans are cooking, mix together a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, the <strong>remaining ground turmeric </strong>and a pinch of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>sugar </strong>– this is your <strong>masala butter</strong></p><p>Once the naans are cooked through and golden brown, brush the <strong>masala butter </strong>over the top – these are your <strong>homemade peshwari naans</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1669725579416-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1669725579416-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1669725579416-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1669725579416-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1669725579416-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, remove the dish from the oven and stir through your <strong>clotted cream</strong> – this is your <strong>baked chicken thigh saag</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>baked chicken thigh saag </strong>alongside the <strong>homemade peshwari naans</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining toasted coconut flakes</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
